WEBVTT

00:11.261 --> 00:12.637
Hello.

00:14.098 --> 00:16.214
-Here you are, my lady.
-Thank you.

00:16.392 --> 00:19.850
It's beautiful, but I feel
self-conscious even borrowing it.

00:20.020 --> 00:22.978
It shouldn't stay hidden
in the LuthorCorp safe.

00:23.148 --> 00:26.936
It needs to be worn for the very ﬁrst time
on the neck of a beautiful woman.

00:27.111 --> 00:28.601
It's perfect, Martha.

00:29.071 --> 00:32.734
But now, it's time to meet
the money bags of Metropolis.

00:32.908 --> 00:37.026
You'll need them to fund your bid
for the United States Senate.

00:41.667 --> 00:43.749
Okay, now remember this is a party.

00:43.919 --> 00:45.125
I know, I know.

00:45.295 --> 00:49.129
Stay away from religion, politics
and bad dye jobs.

00:53.929 --> 00:54.918
Ollie.

00:55.097 --> 00:56.803
It's been too long.

00:56.974 --> 00:58.589
Come over here.

00:58.767 --> 01:00.883
-Hello.
-Hi, Oliver.

01:01.270 --> 01:04.307
Mr. Westoott and his wife, Candice.

01:04.481 --> 01:06.312
I'd like to introduce you to Lois Lane.

01:06.483 --> 01:07.859
Hey.

01:08.485 --> 01:10.646
Simon Westoott.

01:11.155 --> 01:12.315
It's my pleasure.

01:13.073 --> 01:14.153
Likewise.

01:15.492 --> 01:19.076
So I wanted to tell you
that I thought you were so eloquent...

01:19.246 --> 01:21.237
...at the congressional
indictment hearings.

01:24.376 --> 01:25.991
Sorry about your oil tanker.

01:26.378 --> 01:28.790
I'd hate to be a pelican
in that harbor, huh?

01:29.339 --> 01:30.920
Well, we're gonna go.

01:31.759 --> 01:34.045
That's our cue, so....

01:35.554 --> 01:40.674
Guess I forgot to add public humiliation
to the list of cocktail-party don'ts.

01:43.103 --> 01:45.344
I'm gonna go get us a drink, okay?

01:45.522 --> 01:46.602
Just wait here...

01:46.899 --> 01:50.517
...and don't talk to anybody,
okay?

01:59.453 --> 02:02.786
And that you've had a chance
to reconnect with some old friends.

02:02.956 --> 02:05.698
Right now, though, I'd like to introduce
you to someone...

02:05.876 --> 02:07.867
...who I hope will be a new friend.

02:08.045 --> 02:10.502
A valuable new friend.

02:10.672 --> 02:13.379
Someone I'm sure you'll be glad
to have on your side.

02:13.550 --> 02:17.793
Ladies and gentlemen, may I introduce
to you our Kansas state senator...

02:17.971 --> 02:22.214
...and your future United States senator,
Martha Kent.

02:27.898 --> 02:29.058
Thank you very much.

02:35.113 --> 02:36.728
Thank you.

02:37.491 --> 02:38.526
Hey.

02:38.951 --> 02:40.407
Excuse me.

02:48.961 --> 02:50.246
Give me the necklace.

02:51.588 --> 02:53.169
You forgot to say please.

04:10.167 --> 04:14.831
I couldn't ID the guy,
but he didn't exactly stick around to chat.

04:15.672 --> 04:18.880
You told Mr. Luthor
that you almost caught the guy.

04:19.051 --> 04:21.758
Yet you expect me to believe
you didn't see anything?

04:21.929 --> 04:26.798
Look, Lionel Luthor pays SafeTex what,
a gazillion dollars for personal security?

04:26.975 --> 04:30.843
So don't blame me if you let a Boy Scout
with an archery badge crash his party.

04:33.690 --> 04:35.351
Okay.

04:35.525 --> 04:37.902
I think Ms. Lane's made her point.

04:38.195 --> 04:39.310
Wouldn't you say?

04:44.576 --> 04:46.908
She'll call you
if she remembers anything.

04:49.790 --> 04:51.326
Evening.

04:58.590 --> 05:00.581
So, what aren't you telling him?

05:01.510 --> 05:04.547
| just nabbed the story of my life.

05:05.889 --> 05:10.633
William Tell's not the only one who
walked away with a serious party favor.

05:15.023 --> 05:16.399
Mr. Queen?

05:17.526 --> 05:18.857
My mom told me you were here.

05:19.027 --> 05:22.144
Smallville, it's almost midnight.

05:22.531 --> 05:24.487
Smallville?

05:24.658 --> 05:26.273
You're Clark Kent?

05:26.785 --> 05:28.195
You must be Oliver Queen.

05:28.370 --> 05:29.530
Yeah.

05:36.878 --> 05:40.166
This is funny, it's just-- You know,
the way Lois talked about you...

05:40.340 --> 05:43.252
-...I thought you were a little more—
-I could use some water.

05:43.427 --> 05:45.088
Little more what?

05:46.263 --> 05:47.252
Well....

05:47.597 --> 05:48.586
Of a geek?

05:48.765 --> 05:52.349
Well, you're not exactly jumping
the velvet ropes at nightclubs, so....

05:52.644 --> 05:56.262
It's nice to see that Lois has found
someone who can overlook her personality.

05:56.440 --> 05:58.101
Well, don't worry about it, Clark.

05:58.275 --> 06:00.266
If I lived with such a beautiful woman...

06:00.444 --> 06:03.902
...I probably would've masked my feelings
in sarcasm too.

06:05.824 --> 06:08.110
-Feelings?
-Feelings?

06:08.285 --> 06:11.072
Little advice, Freud Jr., there,
stick with your day job.

06:11.246 --> 06:13.157
I'm here to get that necklace back.

06:13.331 --> 06:15.913
Last thing I want is my mom
indebted to Lionel Luthor.

06:16.084 --> 06:20.077
She should have thought of that before
she accepted his help with her fundraising.

06:20.255 --> 06:23.588
If you're really championing
the cause of pick-pocketed billionaires...

06:23.759 --> 06:25.841
...you might wanna add a few more
to the list.

06:26.053 --> 06:28.260
What, Lionel Luthor is not the only victim?

06:28.430 --> 06:31.342
Over a dozen of Metropolis's
who's who have been hit recently.

06:31.683 --> 06:33.093
Good, then there's some leads.

06:33.268 --> 06:36.806
Well, not if all the victims
were as uncooperative as Lionel Luthor.

06:38.440 --> 06:41.557
Do you ﬁnd it interesting
that he never called the police?

06:42.486 --> 06:46.024
Okay, if you boys are done
marking your territory--

06:46.198 --> 06:50.032
Which, for clariﬁcation, is not me.
--l have a front-page article...

06:50.202 --> 06:51.988
...that's missing a few key details.

06:52.162 --> 06:53.493
Good night, boys.

06:53.663 --> 06:55.574
Now, play nice.

07:04.841 --> 07:06.832
What was with that sprint
up the last hill?

07:07.010 --> 07:10.002
| always suspected
you couldn't handle me.

07:13.517 --> 07:14.677
Dr. Groll.

07:15.602 --> 07:16.762
Did we have a meeting?

07:17.229 --> 07:20.016
No, I just need a few words with you...

07:20.732 --> 07:21.892
...in private.

07:22.192 --> 07:24.729
Well, you can say anything
in front of Ms. Lang.

07:24.903 --> 07:27.189
-lt's about the device.
-Please.

07:43.338 --> 07:44.544
Where'd you get that?

07:46.550 --> 07:48.006
I found it.

07:48.718 --> 07:51.095
And I asked Dr. Groll
to ﬁgure out what it was.

07:51.263 --> 07:52.844
Some kind of power source...

07:53.140 --> 07:55.176
...beyond anything developed on Earth.

07:55.350 --> 07:57.215
If we could understand the technology...

07:57.394 --> 07:59.476
...it could solve
the planet's energy crisis.

07:59.646 --> 08:02.058
Well, for someone on the verge
of saving the world...

08:02.232 --> 08:04.644
...your enthusiasm seems tempered.

08:05.777 --> 08:07.392
There is one risk.

08:07.904 --> 08:10.020
If it fell into the wrong hands--

08:10.198 --> 08:12.154
It could be used as a weapon.

08:14.161 --> 08:18.495
So if it's so dangerous,
shouldn't you hand it in to the government?

08:19.416 --> 08:22.249
Then he'd lose any chance
at a Nobel Prize.

08:22.419 --> 08:23.909
Isn't that right, Dr. Groll?

08:25.755 --> 08:27.461
What do you want me to do?

08:30.510 --> 08:33.798
Every breakthrough has its challenges.

08:34.347 --> 08:36.258
Keep working.

08:38.435 --> 08:40.050
Very well.

08:54.201 --> 08:55.782
Hey.

08:56.244 --> 08:57.233
Let me guess.

08:57.412 --> 08:59.869
You need help researching
your next article.

09:00.040 --> 09:02.247
Yeah. The Inquisitor's search engine...

09:02.417 --> 09:05.159
...consists of a highlighter
and the yellow pages.

09:05.337 --> 09:08.750
Does Mrs. Kent know
that you're still moonlighting on her?

09:09.090 --> 09:12.173
Are you kidding me?
I've got this double identity thing down.

09:12.344 --> 09:14.460
Besides, I told her all about it
this morning.

09:14.638 --> 09:16.048
All right.

09:16.223 --> 09:18.965
So, what's the story
worth bringing out the alter-Lois?

09:19.142 --> 09:21.929
Actually, you know, now that we're both
in the same biz...

09:22.103 --> 09:24.515
...I probably shouldn't be
leaking my story.

09:25.273 --> 09:26.888
I can't believe you don't trust me.

09:27.067 --> 09:30.559
It's not all of you I don't trust,
it's just one little side of you.

09:30.737 --> 09:32.523
Lois, I'm not gonna scoop your story.

09:32.697 --> 09:34.813
But watching you bumble
through our database...

09:34.991 --> 09:37.152
...is like watching Clark try and dance.

09:37.327 --> 09:38.316
Come on.

09:38.495 --> 09:40.577
Lois, tell me what you got.

09:42.457 --> 09:43.572
Okay.

09:45.043 --> 09:47.455
l scooped this off the scumbag
before he ran away.

09:47.629 --> 09:49.961
There's some writing on the inside
but it's faded.

09:50.131 --> 09:52.463
Yeah, this could take a little while.

10:52.152 --> 10:56.486
Well, I haven't seen you
since the world was falling down around us.

10:56.656 --> 11:01.901
And I hear you have got yourself
a new landlord.

11:02.245 --> 11:04.452
I assume that Lex
told you we were together.

11:05.582 --> 11:10.292
Mr. Luthor, if you called me here
to discuss my relationship with Lex—

11:10.462 --> 11:13.329
Oh, that would be wildly inappropriate,
wouldn't it?

11:13.757 --> 11:16.715
Unless you consider
that the last time you and I spoke...

11:16.885 --> 11:20.719
...we were discussing
which one of us was going to kill Lex.

11:24.351 --> 11:25.761
He wasn't himself.

11:25.935 --> 11:28.597
But you were. Completely yourself.

11:29.773 --> 11:34.233
And unless I'm mistaken, the discussion
was due to the fact that Lex--

11:34.402 --> 11:36.393
Please sit down.

11:36.571 --> 11:40.780
--was obsessed
with a piece of alien technology...

11:40.950 --> 11:44.909
...inﬁnitely too dangerous
for any of us to comprehend.

11:45.080 --> 11:47.412
Does this sound familiar to you at all?

11:48.416 --> 11:51.783
Mr. Luthor, this is all behind us now.

11:51.961 --> 11:57.046
Well, it's obvious that any trust you
have for me only works in times of crisis.

11:57.217 --> 12:00.801
But we both know, Ms. Lang,
that the crisis is far from over.

12:01.429 --> 12:05.513
-Lex salvaged that piece of technology—
-Why do you think I moved in the mansion?

12:05.850 --> 12:06.839
Please tell me.

12:07.018 --> 12:09.134
Mr. Luthor, I care about Lex.

12:09.312 --> 12:13.055
But part of being with him
is protecting Lex from himself.

12:13.233 --> 12:15.975
I'm not naive,
I know that comes with the territory.

12:16.152 --> 12:18.985
Apparently,
Lex has ﬁnally found his equal.

12:19.614 --> 12:23.232
But watching over him,
that is not enough.

12:23.410 --> 12:25.150
Ms. Lang...

12:25.328 --> 12:30.118
...Lex is using every resource
available to him to unlock the mystery...

12:30.291 --> 12:34.000
...of that Pandora's box that he somehow
managed to get ahold of.

12:36.131 --> 12:37.837
Once he opens it...

12:38.007 --> 12:41.841
...and unleashes
whatever is in it to the world....

12:44.681 --> 12:47.548
Well, we may not be lucky enough
to close it...

12:47.725 --> 12:49.511
...this time.

12:53.356 --> 12:55.062
What do you think we should do?

12:57.944 --> 12:59.855
Destroy it.

13:05.952 --> 13:08.614
"The Green Arrow Bandit."

13:08.788 --> 13:10.699
Doesn't really roll off the tongue.

13:11.791 --> 13:15.750
This guy steals your boss's necklace
and then gasses you and your cousin...

13:15.920 --> 13:17.535
...all within a 24-hour period?

13:17.714 --> 13:19.875
I'd say he's got a thing for you.

13:20.049 --> 13:23.667
Well, when you're my editor,
l'll remember to care what you think.

13:23.970 --> 13:26.177
You know that whole
sugar-and-spice thing?

13:26.347 --> 13:28.474
Never really took with you, did it?

13:29.017 --> 13:30.006
Look...

13:30.185 --> 13:33.643
...Green Arrow, Green Eggs and Ham.
It doesn't matter what I call this guy.

13:33.813 --> 13:37.897
I'm gonna have his face plastered
all over the front page soon enough.

13:39.319 --> 13:40.775
Unless I'm missing something...

13:40.945 --> 13:44.278
...without that ring you're not as close
to ID'ing the guy as you claim.

13:44.449 --> 13:48.658
Yeah, that, well, I might've stretched
the truth just a little.

13:49.287 --> 13:52.495
Okay, well, you know,
it's a good thing that The Inquisitor...

13:52.665 --> 13:54.576
...doesn't pride itself on integrity.

13:57.462 --> 14:02.126
Listen, I don't like the idea of you dangling
yourself out as bait in front of this guy.

14:02.300 --> 14:04.586
Anyone after the Green Arrow
will come after you.

14:04.761 --> 14:07.218
Anyone after the Green Arrow
is a friend of mine...

14:07.388 --> 14:12.303
...and I'll be sitting front and center
with him when they lock this guy up.

14:13.102 --> 14:14.717
Wouldn't want you on myjury.

14:16.814 --> 14:18.429
Meaning?

14:21.110 --> 14:23.101
Well, you know, I thought...

14:23.279 --> 14:26.442
...we did away with the shoot-ﬁrst-ask-
questions-later mentality...

14:26.616 --> 14:28.732
...with covered wagons.

14:29.869 --> 14:33.612
Oh, come on, don't tell me you're
some kind of bleeding-heart paciﬁst?

14:33.790 --> 14:35.951
And that's worse
than a knee-jerk fascist?

14:42.840 --> 14:44.455
All right...

14:45.301 --> 14:47.917
...forget about this guy for the weekend.

14:48.680 --> 14:52.172
I can have you in Cancun
in time for the sunset tonight.

14:52.350 --> 14:55.968
Sipping margaritas, what do you say?

14:59.148 --> 15:02.982
Well, as much as I would love
to be your beach bimbo...

15:03.152 --> 15:06.736
...the only person I'm gonna spend
the weekend with is into leather...

15:06.906 --> 15:10.490
...and has a perverted fetish for archery.

15:29.637 --> 15:31.844
Well, they changed the gate
to the speedway.

15:32.015 --> 15:33.801
Yeah, and why is that?

15:33.975 --> 15:36.216
Well, that's the way it's engineered.

15:36.394 --> 15:37.975
Oh, I understand.

15:38.146 --> 15:39.807
-Thank you.
-All right.

15:40.398 --> 15:42.764
Clark, what a good surprise.

15:42.942 --> 15:44.603
What brings you up here?

15:44.777 --> 15:47.519
-Mom was pretty shaken up after the party.
-Yeah, I know.

15:47.697 --> 15:49.733
In spite of the
impromptu entertainment...

15:49.907 --> 15:53.365
...your mother made a terriﬁc impression
on some very inﬂuential people.

15:53.536 --> 15:56.323
-She wasn't the only one.
-Walk me to my car, will you?

15:56.497 --> 16:00.536
Don't worry, Clark, my security team
is making a very thorough investigation.

16:00.710 --> 16:02.575
Unlike the police.

16:03.296 --> 16:06.288
Why wouldn't you report something
that valuable if it was stolen?

16:06.466 --> 16:08.673
Well, I'd rather not let
the entire city know...

16:08.843 --> 16:11.585
...that I'm a sitting duck
for some acrobatic archer.

16:11.763 --> 16:15.551
It's not wise to advertise
our vulnerabilities, is it, Clark?

16:15.725 --> 16:19.013
We're talking about some
very expensive vulnerabilities.

16:19.187 --> 16:20.552
Oh, Fabergé egg.

16:22.398 --> 16:25.435
"Bishop's miter, 14th-century."
It's big stuff.

16:25.610 --> 16:28.647
Not the kind of stuff you ﬁnd
in your local pawnshop window.

16:30.698 --> 16:33.735
Here's something that might interest you
unless you've noticed.

16:33.910 --> 16:38.700
There's only one name on the SafeTex
client list that hasn't been hit already.

16:40.124 --> 16:42.866
I don't wanna be late. You ﬁnd it, huh?

18:30.651 --> 18:31.811
Who are you?

18:32.195 --> 18:33.981
Haven't you read?

18:34.947 --> 18:36.198
I'm the Green Arrow.

18:38.284 --> 18:41.526
Well, I hope you enjoyed your cult status
while it lasted.

18:41.704 --> 18:45.117
I think you're taking the whole
neighborhood-watch thing too seriously.

18:57.386 --> 19:00.378
-We got a breach. Secure all exits.
-Yes, sir.

19:00.556 --> 19:02.547
That was fun.

19:03.226 --> 19:05.808
Looks like I'm not the only one
with a secret.

19:06.604 --> 19:09.061
Hate to break it to you
but you're on the wrong side.

19:09.232 --> 19:11.348
I'm not sure the police would agree.

19:11.567 --> 19:13.353
Look around you, Beav.

19:13.528 --> 19:16.019
The days of the good guys
running the show are over.

20:04.745 --> 20:06.610
Good evening.

20:16.591 --> 20:18.331
Ms. Lang, what are you doing?

20:19.051 --> 20:21.303
Lionel Luthor knows about the black box.

20:21.470 --> 20:25.429
And he is willing to do anything
to get his hands on it.

20:25.600 --> 20:27.215
And you think I'm working with him?

20:27.393 --> 20:29.008
Not yet.

20:29.937 --> 20:34.522
But trust me, when he approaches you,
and he will...

20:34.692 --> 20:37.775
...Lionel is going to make you an offer
that is hard to resist.

20:38.738 --> 20:40.854
No matter what the bribe...

20:41.157 --> 20:44.820
...you will come to us before you
breathe a word to Lionel Luthor.

20:47.705 --> 20:50.788
With all due respect,
I work for Lex and not his girlfriend.

20:50.958 --> 20:55.668
I'm not interested
in your respect, Dr Groll.

20:56.464 --> 21:01.675
I'm much more interested
in your 14 years of employment here.

21:02.219 --> 21:06.087
Your two girls that are now
in prestigious prep schools.

21:06.265 --> 21:08.927
That new home that you just built
on Sparling Lane.

21:11.103 --> 21:13.765
You have a pretty wonderful life.

21:16.359 --> 21:17.599
Are you threatening me?

21:17.944 --> 21:21.061
Well, it just came to my attention
that if the government...

21:21.238 --> 21:25.857
...or your colleagues were to ﬁnd out that
you were secretly testing alien weapons...

21:26.619 --> 21:29.736
...this life that you have
worked so hard for...

21:30.122 --> 21:32.829
...may take an unfortunate turn.

21:52.770 --> 21:55.227
So how'd you let this guy
slip through your ﬁngers?

21:55.398 --> 21:58.231
This Green Arrow Bandit's
got a lot of gadgets.

21:58.401 --> 21:59.436
Gadgets?

21:59.610 --> 22:00.816
Against the man of steel?

22:01.821 --> 22:03.436
He's good, all right?

22:03.614 --> 22:06.105
Fine, backing off.

22:06.283 --> 22:07.784
"The Green Arrow Bandit"?

22:07.952 --> 22:10.659
Is that really the name
Lois came up with?

22:10.830 --> 22:14.197
If you ask me, I'd lose the "bandit,"
but not my story.

22:14.375 --> 22:17.993
With your competitive streak,
I'm surprised you forfeited this one to Lois.

22:18.796 --> 22:20.912
Competition? Lois?

22:21.090 --> 22:23.547
-l'm chalking this one up to pro bono.
-Yeah, right.

22:23.759 --> 22:26.091
Okay, so idle hands
aren't really my thing.

22:26.262 --> 22:28.719
I got the SafeTex report on the arrows.

22:29.015 --> 22:32.428
They're made from an advanced
titanium alloy that is untraceable.

22:33.060 --> 22:35.517
-What about the ring?
-None of the shots I scanned...

22:35.688 --> 22:37.519
...came out to have a clean image.

22:38.482 --> 22:41.189
However, I may have forgotten
to mention to Lois...

22:41.360 --> 22:44.978
...that my computer is compiling
them to render a new one.

22:51.162 --> 22:55.622
Look, you can tell the mailroom
to stop forwarding these bogus claims.

22:55.791 --> 22:59.625
Well, I highly doubt the Green Arrow
is going to out himself...

22:59.795 --> 23:01.251
...on a Hello Kitty notepad.

23:01.422 --> 23:03.583
Yeah. Thanks.

23:20.066 --> 23:21.146
Come here.

23:25.488 --> 23:28.730
-Lois, hey.
-Chloe!

23:29.909 --> 23:31.274
-Lois?
-Help.

23:31.869 --> 23:33.484
Please.

23:33.662 --> 23:35.493
Clark, she's in trouble.

23:42.963 --> 23:44.578
Lois?

23:46.258 --> 23:48.169
Looks like someone took her.

23:52.014 --> 23:54.130
Took her? What? Who would do that?

23:54.308 --> 23:55.673
Isn't it obvious?

23:55.851 --> 23:56.931
The Green Arrow.

23:58.854 --> 24:01.641
What makes you think
he'd have anything to do with this?

24:02.274 --> 24:05.357
He's wanted all over town
for armed robbery.

24:05.528 --> 24:09.237
Lois is the one who publicly threatened
to unmask the guy.

24:09.406 --> 24:11.943
Guess he doesn't live by a code of honor.

24:15.454 --> 24:17.069
Because it's not the same as yours?

24:17.540 --> 24:21.158
If you're as interested in ﬁnding out
about him as you are in catching him...

24:21.335 --> 24:25.499
...you'd realize that everything he's stolen
has been bought off the black market.

24:26.423 --> 24:28.459
-You saying Lionel's necklace is—?
-Yeah.

24:28.884 --> 24:31.045
That's exactly what I'm saying.

24:31.387 --> 24:34.550
You've been on this hunt
to return it to its original thief.

24:37.226 --> 24:38.432
You think Lionel took her?

24:38.894 --> 24:40.634
There's a lot of people that would...

24:40.813 --> 24:43.179
...go to any length
to catch the Green Arrow.

25:02.877 --> 25:04.367
I gotta go.

25:07.214 --> 25:09.421
Chloe, it's too late,
there's no sign of her.

25:09.592 --> 25:13.255
I might have something that will help.
The image from the ring ﬁnally rendered.

25:13.429 --> 25:15.590
And I'm sending it to you right now.

25:18.517 --> 25:22.430
It's a family crest. The only problem is,
ye olde crest makers weren't very creative.

25:22.605 --> 25:25.221
There's thousands of them
and they're all identical.

25:25.399 --> 25:28.391
It's gonna take me a little while
to track this one down.

25:30.321 --> 25:32.437
-I've seen this before.
-Clark?

25:34.491 --> 25:35.992
Hello?

25:37.203 --> 25:38.693
Hello?

26:45.521 --> 26:46.977
Tracking system enabled.

26:48.232 --> 26:50.439
Transmitting to BIackBeny.

26:50.609 --> 26:52.395
Tracking engaged.

26:53.070 --> 26:55.402
Tracking Safe Tex Security.

26:55.572 --> 26:57.824
Tracking system enabled.

26:57.992 --> 27:00.324
Tracking Safe Tex Security.

27:00.536 --> 27:02.993
-No. Let me go.
-Shut up.

27:03.872 --> 27:05.954
Get your hands off me.

27:07.710 --> 27:10.292
Let me go. Hey!

27:18.971 --> 27:20.632
What do you know about Green Arrow?

27:20.806 --> 27:24.219
I should've known he wouldn't have
the stones to face me in person.

27:27.229 --> 27:28.218
