27:36.905 --> 27:38.190
You know who he is.

27:38.657 --> 27:39.942
Give me a name.

27:40.326 --> 27:41.406
What did you see?

27:56.091 --> 27:58.343
-Who's the Green Arrow?
-Bandit.

27:58.510 --> 28:01.422
Green Arrow Bandit.
And like you don't know.

28:01.597 --> 28:04.213
That Errol-Flynn wannabe
put you guys up to this.

28:06.268 --> 28:08.133
That's enough.

28:12.775 --> 28:15.687
This "Bandit"...

28:15.861 --> 28:19.729
...has made a joke of the ﬁrm
I've worked my life to build.

28:20.115 --> 28:24.028
He's walked off
with more than 30 million from my clients.

28:24.203 --> 28:26.910
Then why am I the one with bruises
on my knees right now?

28:27.081 --> 28:30.414
Because you splashed my humiliation...

28:30.584 --> 28:33.291
...across the front page of the paper.

28:33.462 --> 28:35.919
And now you're gonna help me
rectify that.

28:36.090 --> 28:37.796
I don't know who he is.

28:56.318 --> 28:58.684
She doesn't know anything.

28:59.405 --> 29:00.861
Kill her.

30:22.488 --> 30:25.730
I didn't know blackmail
was one of your talents.

30:31.788 --> 30:33.403
Lex...

30:33.582 --> 30:36.745
...I know I went behind your back,
but I wanted to do this my way.

30:36.919 --> 30:39.877
-And if you're mad--
-Actually, I'm impressed.

30:48.514 --> 30:50.755
I've never had anyone...

30:50.933 --> 30:53.094
...try to protect me like that.

30:57.314 --> 31:00.056
Lex, we have a serious problem.

31:00.234 --> 31:02.020
Your father.

31:03.820 --> 31:06.732
He isn't gonna stop until he gets
that black box away from you.

31:08.283 --> 31:10.660
Because he's afraid of what I'll do.

31:12.162 --> 31:14.118
What about you?

31:14.373 --> 31:17.365
Is there a part of you
that wonders the same thing?

31:18.752 --> 31:20.253
No.

31:21.213 --> 31:23.249
I believe in you.

31:25.759 --> 31:27.295
But, Lex...

31:27.469 --> 31:31.257
...there is something that I haven't been
completely honest with you about.

31:36.311 --> 31:38.097
I knew the box was a weapon.

31:46.363 --> 31:49.025
If the box is that dangerous...

31:49.908 --> 31:53.025
...you want me to shut the project down,
don't you?

31:55.956 --> 31:57.662
No.

31:58.417 --> 32:02.786
Lex, it might be the only thing
that will save us from them next time.

32:37.456 --> 32:38.787
Are you okay?

32:41.168 --> 32:42.749
No thanks to you.

32:49.551 --> 32:51.587
-I saved you.
-Yeah.

32:51.762 --> 32:54.253
From goons who were trying to ﬁnd you.

32:54.431 --> 32:57.923
They're not the only one with a
V for Vendetta on your little leather ass.

32:58.101 --> 32:59.181
Little?

32:59.353 --> 33:01.218
I've been working the glutes lately too.

33:01.396 --> 33:03.136
Did the humor come with the costume?

33:03.315 --> 33:07.024
Did the Tomb Raider routine come
from wanting Daddy's attention?

33:12.991 --> 33:14.777
I guess my aim's a little rusty.

33:15.285 --> 33:16.491
Now...

33:18.246 --> 33:22.990
...let's take off those glasses and unveil
our prince of thieves, shall we?

33:52.948 --> 33:54.154
Oliver Queen.

33:54.783 --> 33:55.943
You owe me one.

34:03.750 --> 34:05.035
That was you on the roof?

34:07.504 --> 34:08.835
Why'd you let me get away?

34:12.008 --> 34:16.342
I'm not sure Lois would understand
why her new boyfriend leads a double life.

34:20.434 --> 34:23.141
Or why one of her best friends
does the same thing?

34:25.230 --> 34:26.640
I think we're even.

34:26.815 --> 34:30.148
We'll be even when you return
what you stole from Lionel.

34:50.505 --> 34:51.756
Chloe, what's all the buzz?

34:51.923 --> 34:54.505
Seven stolen artifacts were
anonymously returned...

34:54.676 --> 34:56.541
...to the Met, the Tate and the Louvre.

34:56.720 --> 35:00.087
Looks like you got some competition
in the knight-in-shining-armor arena.

35:00.265 --> 35:03.177
The guy does a couple good things
and goes from villain to hero?

35:03.351 --> 35:06.514
Clark, every time he strikes
some corrupt tycoon...

35:06.688 --> 35:09.600
...an anonymous donation to some charity
appears the next day.

35:09.775 --> 35:12.107
You don't care how many laws
are broken to get it?

35:12.277 --> 35:16.020
I guess that's the price of justice. If you
ask me, he's a modem-day Robin Hood.

35:16.198 --> 35:19.531
That still doesn't mean I'm not dying
to ﬁnd out who he is, though.

35:19.701 --> 35:23.569
Oh, hey, I never heard back from you
after I sent you the picture of that crest.

35:23.747 --> 35:26.033
I kind of ran into a dead end.

35:29.503 --> 35:31.084
That's funny, so did I.

35:32.506 --> 35:35.122
All my ﬁles on the ring are gone.

35:35.467 --> 35:37.708
Including the backup ﬁles. Clark?

35:39.679 --> 35:42.056
Just don't look into him, Chloe.

35:45.727 --> 35:48.093
You know who he is, don't you?

35:48.480 --> 35:51.392
As a favor to me, please don't.

35:54.110 --> 35:55.816
And he knows who you are.

35:57.113 --> 36:01.903
Well, I guess there's some sort of secret
code of honor among superheroes.

36:13.171 --> 36:14.160
What do we have here?

36:15.674 --> 36:16.663
Not bad for a rookie.

36:16.842 --> 36:21.586
Incredible. You have every newspaper in the
country calling this guy the Green Arrow.

36:22.055 --> 36:23.261
He's got a real following.

36:23.431 --> 36:25.513
Yeah, well, so did Charles Manson.

36:29.980 --> 36:34.349
I know this is a rare moment for you, but,
you know, maybe you're overreacting.

36:34.526 --> 36:38.690
-lt's not like this guy's a killer.
-Ollie, he's a threat to Metropolis...

36:38.864 --> 36:41.947
...and I'm not gonna stop
until I ﬁnd out who he is.

36:42.617 --> 36:46.109
Trust me. You don't know
the Green Arrow like I do.

37:04.222 --> 37:09.307
Not that I'd ever question
your theatrical skills...

37:10.145 --> 37:12.602
...but you really had Lana convinced.

37:14.482 --> 37:15.562
Thank you, Dad.

37:16.443 --> 37:18.308
Just following the script.

37:18.486 --> 37:20.477
The script that you gave me, son.

37:23.491 --> 37:27.450
But, you know, if you really want to have
a honest relationship with Lana...

37:27.621 --> 37:29.327
...you should stop testing her.

37:32.125 --> 37:34.491
Well, I had to be sure.

37:36.421 --> 37:39.504
Another important lesson you taught me:

37:40.050 --> 37:43.508
"The greater the trust,
the greater the betrayal."

37:47.349 --> 37:51.843
All right, Lex, what do I have to do to prove
to you that I wanna be a part of your life?

37:53.605 --> 37:56.597
Part of my life or part of the project?

37:57.692 --> 38:01.651
I would never have told you about the box
if you hadn't already known.

38:03.949 --> 38:07.487
But that's as close
as you're ever gonna get to it.

38:14.042 --> 38:16.829
So, what makes you think
that I won't tell Lana Lang...

38:17.003 --> 38:21.838
...about the obstacle course you set up
for her, if I'm so untrustworthy?

38:25.845 --> 38:31.181
Because you've put so much effort into
fooling the Kents that you're a good man...

38:31.768 --> 38:34.054
...you're starting to believe it yourself.

38:56.167 --> 38:58.909
I didn't realize
I was such a fascinating subject.

39:00.880 --> 39:02.916
You've been reading up on me.

39:03.216 --> 39:05.047
You and Lois ought to start a fan club.

39:08.221 --> 39:09.927
Are you gonna tell her?

39:11.516 --> 39:15.054
I don't know, Clark. You seem to be doing
a pretty good job skating by...

39:15.228 --> 39:16.889
...with this farm-boy charade.

39:17.480 --> 39:20.893
You can't be with someone
unless they know who you really are.

39:21.484 --> 39:22.940
Trust me, I've tried.

39:24.070 --> 39:26.106
You lost her to Lex.

39:29.534 --> 39:31.525
Is that why you hate me, Clark?

39:32.078 --> 39:35.411
Because I'm just another silver-spoon-fed
rich boy, is that it?

39:37.792 --> 39:40.408
Or is it because I won't play
the martyr like you?

39:40.587 --> 39:43.329
You can play this game
as long as you want.

39:43.882 --> 39:46.294
But sooner or later you're gonna hurt her.

39:47.010 --> 39:47.999
You know that.

39:49.846 --> 39:52.462
Well, you seem to have all the answers.

39:52.640 --> 39:56.132
So I guess it's a good thing I've decided
to put this into safer hands.

40:02.400 --> 40:06.484
For the record, Lionel bought that
off a notorious Bosnian warlord...

40:06.654 --> 40:08.485
...used it to launder LuthorCorp money.

40:08.656 --> 40:10.612
So why give it to me?

40:13.870 --> 40:17.863
Well, you seem to have a crystal-clear idea
of what's right and what's wrong.

40:18.083 --> 40:19.948
You decide who it belongs to.

40:23.505 --> 40:25.962
It's not as clear as it used to be.

40:27.967 --> 40:31.801
You really think it's right to steal
as long as it goes to a good cause?

40:32.013 --> 40:34.675
That the end justiﬁes the means?

40:35.350 --> 40:37.136
Absolutely, yes.

40:38.853 --> 40:40.889
I'll never feel that way.

40:47.487 --> 40:49.318
You said you didn't owe me one.

40:49.489 --> 40:50.854
So why are you really here?

40:53.284 --> 40:57.744
Clark, you have abilities
I couldn't even dream of.

40:59.624 --> 41:03.367
And I admire that you use them
to save the people you're close to.

41:03.920 --> 41:05.410
But...?

41:06.089 --> 41:09.206
But there's a whole world
of people out there, Clark.

41:09.384 --> 41:10.874
They need us.

41:14.305 --> 41:16.387
With your potential...

41:18.393 --> 41:21.100
...you can't wait for them
to come to you.

41:25.608 --> 41:28.224
When you're ready
to do something about that...

41:30.280 --> 41:32.111
...you let me know.

42:14.616 --> 42:16.607
[ENGLISH]
